I think the &quot;is this evidence worth a legal fight?&quot; question/advice is right
on.  This was &quot;their group&quot; and whether they have a legal leg to stand on or
not, IMHO the more important question is this: if you are forming a new
group, do you want any publicity at all that associates you with this other
flakey group?  



Start fresh . start clean.  



I&#39;ve been in this exact same situation: I am content that the evidence I
collected on the outings with the Flakey Crew I used to belong to was
interesting.  But I don&#39;t need to share that evidence with others to prove
myself to anyone.  If you are half as serious about this as you sound,
you&#39;ll have a bucketful of your own evidence before you know it.



-          Doug H


